{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MESqxK1ffpTeaQisnEd1Qz","type":"tool_result","content":"   160→1. Its own previous state h^k_{t-1}\n   161→2. The current input x_t (through its own W_x^k, W_h^k, b^k parameters)\n   162→\n   163→There is NO cross-head communication in the state dynamics. -/\n   164→theorem e1h_heads_independent {h : ℕ} (model : E1HModel h d d) (T : ℕ)\n   165→    (inputs : Fin T → (Fin d → ℝ)) (h1 h2 : Fin h) :\n   166→    let state := e1hMultiHeadState model T inputs\n   167→    ∀ (head2' : E1HHead d d),\n   168→      let model' : E1HModel h d d := { model with\n   169→        heads := fun i => if i = h2 then head2' else model.heads i }\n   170→      let state' := e1hMultiHeadState model' T inputs\n   171→      h1 ≠ h2 → state h1 = state' h1 := by\n   172→  intro state head2' model' state' h_neq\n   173→  simp only [e1hMultiHeadState, e1hHeadStateAfterT]\n   174→  have h_heads_eq : model'.heads h1 = model.heads h1 := by\n   175→    simp only [model']\n   176→    split_ifs with h_eq\n   177→    · exact absurd h_eq h_neq\n   178→    · rfl\n   179→  rw [h_heads_eq]\n   180→\n   181→/-- Heads can be computed in parallel (no sequential dependency between heads) -/\n   182→theorem e1h_heads_parallel_computable {h : ℕ} (model : E1HModel h d d) (T : ℕ)\n   183→    (inputs : Fin T → (Fin d → ℝ)) :\n   184→    ∀ h1 h2 : Fin h, h1 ≠ h2 →\n   185→      let state := e1hMultiHeadState model T inputs\n   186→      state h1 = e1hHeadStateAfterT (model.heads h1) T inputs (fun _ => 0) ∧\n   187→      state h2 = e1hHeadStateAfterT (model.heads h2) T inputs (fun _ => 0) := by\n   188→  intro h1 h2 _\n   189→  exact ⟨rfl, rfl⟩\n   190→\n   191→/-! ## Part 5: Temporal Depth -/\n   192→\n   193→/-- E1H has compositional depth T per layer (same as E88).\n   194→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6291cb2-b975-4ff1-9999-75725616ecec","uuid":"2fd8a812-87ea-495b-9ba4-e9263bf921d8","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/erikg/elman-proofs/ElmanProofs/Expressivity/E1HDefinition.lean","content":"1. Its own previous state h^k_{t-1}\n2. The current input x_t (through its own W_x^k, W_h^k, b^k parameters)\n\nThere is NO cross-head communication in the state dynamics. -/\ntheorem e1h_heads_independent {h : ℕ} (model : E1HModel h d d) (T : ℕ)\n    (inputs : Fin T → (Fin d → ℝ)) (h1 h2 : Fin h) :\n    let state := e1hMultiHeadState model T inputs\n    ∀ (head2' : E1HHead d d),\n      let model' : E1HModel h d d := { model with\n        heads := fun i => if i = h2 then head2' else model.heads i }\n      let state' := e1hMultiHeadState model' T inputs\n      h1 ≠ h2 → state h1 = state' h1 := by\n  intro state head2' model' state' h_neq\n  simp only [e1hMultiHeadState, e1hHeadStateAfterT]\n  have h_heads_eq : model'.heads h1 = model.heads h1 := by\n    simp only [model']\n    split_ifs with h_eq\n    · exact absurd h_eq h_neq\n    · rfl\n  rw [h_heads_eq]\n\n/-- Heads can be computed in parallel (no sequential dependency between heads) -/\ntheorem e1h_heads_parallel_computable {h : ℕ} (model : E1HModel h d d) (T : ℕ)\n    (inputs : Fin T → (Fin d → ℝ)) :\n    ∀ h1 h2 : Fin h, h1 ≠ h2 →\n      let state := e1hMultiHeadState model T inputs\n      state h1 = e1hHeadStateAfterT (model.heads h1) T inputs (fun _ => 0) ∧\n      state h2 = e1hHeadStateAfterT (model.heads h2) T inputs (fun _ => 0) := by\n  intro h1 h2 _\n  exact ⟨rfl, rfl⟩\n\n/-! ## Part 5: Temporal Depth -/\n\n/-- E1H has compositional depth T per layer (same as E88).\n","numLines":35,"startLine":160,"totalLines":305}}}
